### Instrumenting Web Frameworks with newrelic.instrumentWebframework() in Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

The `newrelic.instrumentWebframework()` method and `WebFrameworkShim` are used for instrumenting Node.js web frameworks like `restify` or `express`. This helps in tracing web requests and responses within the New Relic monitoring system. It requires the `newrelic` module to be imported.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');
const express = require('express');

const app = express();

// Example usage with Express
newrelic.instrumentWebframework(app, function() {
  // Instrumentation logic for Express
  console.log('Express web framework instrumented');
});

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello World!');
});

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server listening on port 3000');
});
```

