### Node.js - Langchain setLlmTokenCountCallback API

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This code snippet demonstrates the addition of the `setLlmTokenCountCallback` API endpoint. This allows developers to register a custom callback function for calculating token counts, which is essential for accurate AI monitoring when default methods are insufficient.

```javascript
// Example of using setLlmTokenCountCallback (conceptual)
// Requires the New Relic agent to be initialized.

const newrelic = require('newrelic');

function customTokenCounter(text) {
  // Implement custom logic to count tokens
  return text.split('\s+').length; // Simple word count as example
}

newrelic.setLlmTokenCountCallback(customTokenCounter);
```

