### Start Custom Segments with Callbacks or Promises (Node.js)

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

Introduces `newrelic.startSegment()` as a replacement for `newrelic.createTracer()`. This API allows developers to create custom performance monitoring segments within their Node.js applications using either traditional callbacks or modern Promises. It's useful for tracking the execution time of specific code blocks or asynchronous operations.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

// Using callbacks
newrelic.startSegment('myCallbackSegment', function() {
  // Code to be traced
  setTimeout(() => {
    console.log('Callback executed');
  }, 100);
});

// Using promises
newrelic.startSegment('myPromiseSegment', async function() {
  // Code to be traced
  await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 100));
  console.log('Promise resolved');
});

```

